        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 8 at 8:13PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 813 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles south of Wheeless, or 16 miles northeast of Clayton, moving
east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Felt and Wheeless.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
